ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Number of months between phase start date and end date in Phase 1/1A
Notes: 1 month is defined as 28 days

ElementDescription: Number of months between phase start date and end date in Phase 1B
Notes: 1 month is defined as 28 days

ElementDescription: Number of months between phase start date and end date in Phase 2
Notes: 1 month is defined as 28 days

ElementDescription: Number of months between phase start date and end date in Phase 3
Notes: 1 month is defined as 28 days

ElementDescription: Censored in Phase 1/1A
Notes: 1= if patient completed both the phase and study; 0 otherwise

ElementDescription: Censored in Phase 1B
Notes: 1= if patient completed both the phase and study; 0 otherwise

ElementDescription: Censored in Phase 2
Notes: 1= if patient completed both the phase and study; 0 otherwise

ElementDescription: P1  patient's duration in phase was truncated to 74 days after the last patient visit
Notes: "1= if patient's duration in phase was truncated to 74 days after the last patient visit (necessary for some patients who were lost to follow-up but the site recorded a phase discontinuation date longer than 74 days after last patient contact. 74 days is 2 months after the visit, including a 2-week visit window); missing otherwise"

ElementDescription: P1B  patient's duration in phase was truncated to 74 days after the last patient visit
Notes: "1= if patient's duration in phase was truncated to 74 days after the last patient visit (necessary for some patients who were lost to follow-up but the site recorded a phase discontinuation date longer than 74 days after last patient contact. 74 days is 2 months after the visit, including a 2-week visit window); missing otherwise"

ElementDescription: P2  patient's duration in phase was truncated to 74 days after the last patient visit
Notes: "1= if patient's duration in phase was truncated to 74 days after the last patient visit (necessary for some patients who were lost to follow-up but the site recorded a phase discontinuation date longer than 74 days after last patient contact. 74 days is 2 months after the visit, including a 2-week visit window); missing otherwise"

ElementDescription: patient discontinued phase 1/1A due to lack of efficacy
Notes: 1= if patient discontinued phase 1/1A due to lack of efficacy; 0 otherwise

ElementDescription: patient discontinued phase 2 due to lack of efficacy
Notes: 1= if patient discontinued phase 2 due to lack of efficacy; 0 otherwise

ElementDescription: patient discontinued phase 1/1A due to unacceptable side effects
Notes: 1= if patient discontinued phase 1/1A due to unacceptable side effects; 0 otherwise

ElementDescription: patient discontinued phase 2 due to unacceptable side effects
Notes: 1= if patient discontinued phase 2 due to unacceptable side effects; 0 otherwise

Notes: 1= if patient discontinued phase 1/1A due to patient/subject advocate's decision; 0 otherwise

Notes: 1= if patient discontinued phase 2 due to patient/subject advocate's decision; 0 otherwise

ElementDescription: Time (months) with Successful Treatment
Notes: Number of months in Phase 1/1A patient has CGIS response=1

ElementDescription: Composite Ordinal Effectiveness Outcome
Notes: for Phase 1/1A: 1=Completed with improvement; 2=Discontinued with Improvement; 3=Completed w/o improvement; 4=Discontinued w/o Improvement; 5=Discontinued for Safety

ElementDescription: P1 patient discontinued phase due to patient/subject advocate's decision AND the patient went on to the next phase
Notes: 1= if patient discontinued phase due to patient/subject advocate's decision AND the patient went on to the next phase; 0 otherwise

ElementDescription: P2 patient discontinued phase due to patient/subject advocate's decision AND the patient went on to the next phase
Notes: 1= if patient discontinued phase due to patient/subject advocate's decision AND the patient went on to the next phase; 0 otherwise
